description: ShaMaran Petroleum Corp., together with its subsidiaries, engages in the exploration and development of oil and gas. The company holds a 27.6% interest in the Atrush Block production sharing contract, which covers an area of 269 square kilometers located in the Kurdistan region of Iraq. It also provides technical and administration services. ShaMaran Petroleum Corp. was incorporated in 1991 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
